terpreted to fit the constantly changing "reality" of the society; they assume different meanings at different times. The conflicts and resulting compromises over a hundred-year period have provided a sense of history that allows each group to define, develop, adapt and sustain their sense of belonging to their own communities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aAliensxSpainxDeià. 0aAlienszSpainzDeià. 0aNoncitizenszSpainzDeỉ. 0aTourismxSocial aspectsxSpainxDeià. 0aTourismxSocial aspectszSpainzDeià. 0aTourismxSocial aspectszSpainzDeià. 0aVisitors, ForeignxSpainxDeià. 0aVisitors, ForeignzSpainzDeià. 0aVisitors, ForeignzSpainzDeià. 7aTravel / Europe / Spain & Portugal.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311099828340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781782381860?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782381860423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782381860/original  a978-3-11-099828-3  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK